Responsibilities:

         Supervise and monitor the site progress and subcontractors performance;
         Assist Project Manager for day-to-day operation, prepare method statement and shop drawings;
         Attend weekly, monthly meets with main contractors;
         Handle and resolve site constrain and site problem.

 Requirements - Qualification:

         Higher Diploma / Degree holder or above in Civil Engineering disciplines;
         Minimum 7 years of civil works site experience;
         Holder of Valid green card;
         Proficiency in Microsoft Office, Microsoft Project and Chinese word processing;
         Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.
         Candidates with less experiences will be considered as Project Engineer.
         Alternative Saturday off per month at once. 
         Location:  Kowloon / New Territories

You will be assigned to work in our client's workplace for providing the following services:

Responsibilities:
(i) To manage and supervise Works Supervisor Support;
(ii) To supervise the contractor's pedestrian and road improvement schemes initiated by Energizing Kowloon East Office;
(iii)To carry out site audit checking and measurement on contractor’s works;
(iv) To keep records and report progress and prepare relevant returns;
(v) To apply for the excavation permit for the site works; and
(vI) To perform any other duties assigned by Seniors.

Requirements:
(i) obtained a Diploma or Higher Certificate in Civil Engineering or Building Studies or other construction/building-related subjects from a Hong Kong polytechnic university / polytechnic, the Hong Kong Institute of Vocational Education or a technical institute / technical college, or equivalent;

(ii)

have 5 years' relevant experience; or
have 3 years' relevant experience, one of which should be at Works Supervisor I level; or
have 3 years' relevant post-qualification experience; and
(iii) Level 2 or Grade E above in English Language and Chinese Language in HKDSE or HKCEE,or equivalent.

The Role:

Supervise the sequence of excavation and installation of temporary works;
Check the depth of excavation and the quality of retrieved material at the founding stratum;
Ensure quality of work, safety and timely completion of projects in a cost-effective manner.
The Person:

Higher Diploma / Higher Certificate in civil/ structural/ geotechnical engineering;
Minimum 10-year relevant experience in construction work project;
Experienced in project management.

